4 A JOINT RESOLUTION OF THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
5 MONTANA REQUESTING AN INTERIM STUDY OF ETHICS; AND REQUIRING THAT THE FINAL RESULTS
6 OF THE STUDY BE REPORTED TO THE 70TH LEGISLATURE.
7
8 WHEREAS, Article XIII, section 4, of the Montana Constitution states: "The legislature shall provide a
9 code of ethics prohibiting conflict between public duty and private interest for members of the legislature and all
10 state and local officers and employees"; and
11 WHEREAS, the Legislature enacted a code of ethics in 1977, which is codified in Title 2, chapter 2, part
12 1, MCA; and
13 WHEREAS, the Joint Rules of the Legislature, the Senate Rules, and the House Rules also provide
14 ethics rules applicable to the Legislature; and
15 WHEREAS, under section 2-2-136(1)(a), MCA, the Commissioner of Political Practices has a role in
16 the enforcement of the code of ethics but does not have jurisdiction for a complaint concerning a legislator if a
17 legislative act is involved in the complaint; and
18 WHEREAS, the Senate Ethics Committee and the body of the Senate have considered ethical issues
19 during this 69th legislative session and that experience may guide a study.
20
21 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
22 THE STATE OF MONTANA:
23 That the Legislative Council study ethics issues. The study must include:
24 (1) developing a process grounded in legislative procedure for adjudicating ethics issues;
25 (2) determining where there are overlaps or gaps between the authority of the Legislature and the
26 Commissioner of Political Practices; and
27 (3) considering revisions to the code of ethics and legislative rules that the Legislative Council
28 considers necessary and expedient.
